Description: Bangle comprising a flat penannular iron band with overlapping ends; the band is formed of joined ovals.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: John de Monins Johnson
Curator's comments: Cf., lead bangle in Petrie 1927, no. 91. Same or similar bangle depicted in Griffith Institute Archive J. de M. Johnson excavation photograph (O’Connell forthcoming, fig. 111). O’Connell, Elisabeth R. Forthcoming. John de Monins Johnson’s 1913/14 Egypt Exploration Fund expedition to Antinoupolis (Antinoë), with appendix of objects, in Antinoupolis II: Scavi e material III, ed. R. Pintaudi. Florence: Istituto papirologico “G. Vitelli.” Petrie, W. M. F. 1927. Objects of daily use. BSAE 42. London: Quaritch.
Bibliographic references: O'Connell et al 2014 / Antinoupolis at the British Museum (38)
